diskimage_builder/elements/yum/bin/insta.message:
ndisc6 should become available as RDO get's CentOS 8 support.

If we want diskimage-builder to fail the image build when packages are missing; it did'nt on CentOS 7; we may want to revert this at some point.

I believe we can also resolve the CentOS 8 issue by extending the pkg-map[1] to also take into account the Release number. Something like below, but we'd then have to change that once ndisc6 is available in RDO for CentOS 8.

{
  "relese": {
    "centos":
       "7": {
          "ndisc6": "ndisc6"
       }
       "8": {
          "ndisc6": ""
       }
    }
  },
  "family": {
    "redhat": {
      "dhcp-client": "dhclient",
      "ndisc6": "ndisc6"
    },
    "gentoo": {
      "dhcp-client": "net-misc/dhcpcd",
      "ndisc6": "net-misc/ndisc6"
    },
    "suse": {
      "dhcp-client": "dhcp-client"
    },
    "debian": {
      "ifupdown": "ifupdown",
      "ndisc6": "ndisc6"
    }
  },
  "default": {
    "dhcp-client": "isc-dhcp-client",
    "ifupdown": "",
    "ndisc6": ""
  }
}



[1] https://review.opendev.org/#/c/692110/13/diskimage_builder/elements/dhcp-all-interfaces/pkg-map
